<HEADLINE>
FT  19 AUG 92 / Travellers may face tougher laws
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
STRONGER controls on those who park illegally or without permission are
being considered by the government because of concern at the behaviour of
groups such as travellers, Sir George Young, housing and planning minister,
said yesterday.
The proposals include making it a criminal offence to park a caravan on any
land without the landowner's consent, and giving local authorities powers to
tow away illegally parked caravans and seize caravans as an alternative to
fines in the last resort.
Local authorities would no longer be obliged to provide caravan sites for
gypsies. Travellers in England and Wales would have to acquire land for
sites and apply for planning permission in the normal way.
