<TEXT>
GERMAN Environment Minister Klaus Topfer yesterday presented a draft
regulation which would make it compulsory for car makers to take back their
old cars when they are ready for the scrap heap, Reuter reports from Bonn.
Under the draft, German motorists would be entitled to return their old cars
and lorries free of charge to their dealer for disposal or recycling.
The ministry said the regulation, which must still be approved by the
cabinet, would apply to German as well as foreign manufacturers selling
vehicles in Germany. About 2.6m cars are scrapped annually there, most
ending up in crushing plants.
