<TEXT>
ROUSSEL-UCLAF, the French chemicals group, yesterday announced an 18.7 per
cent fall in interim net profits to FFr188m (Dollars 37.67m) in the first
half of 1992, compared with the same period last year.
The news of Roussel's decline in profits is the latest in a series of gloomy
