fell by 1.17 per cent to 1,737.
Roussel fared well in some markets during the first half, notably in health
care products, but suffered in others, particularly in veterinary products
where it has been hit by the economic problems of the former Soviet states.
The group mustered a modest 3.2 per cent increase in sales to FFr7.34bn in
the first half, and held the fall in net profits to 5 per cent on a
comparable basis, allowing for restructuring and exceptional items.
