   By IAN HAMILTON FAZEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Quicks Group, the Manchester-based vehicles and parts distributor, turned in
a more than three-fold increase, from Pounds 310,000 to Pounds 1.11m, in
interim pre-tax profits, writes Ian Hamilton Fazey.
Turnover for the six months to June 30 fell to Pounds 99.4m (Pounds 107.1m),
but cost-cutting and moves to raise margins kept operating profits at Pounds
2.01m, only down Pounds 10,000.
