recession. The company made only Pounds 58,000 pre-tax in 1991 after losing
Pounds 896,000 in 1990.
It was hit by difficulties in its leasing division, from which it is
disengaging.
Earnings per share rose to 4.4p (1.4p). The interim dividend is raised to
1.75p (1p), payable from earnings of 4.4p (1.4p) per share.
