FT  18 AUG 92 / BA cabin staff to decide on action
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THOUSANDS of passengers could face further disruption on British Airways
domestic and European flights as a result of the dispute with cabin crew
members of the TGWU general union.
The crews will today consider another one-day strike over new terms and
conditions. BA has made what it describes as a final offer and warned that
if cabin crew staff take action they could be suspended.
The dispute is over compensation for new terms and conditions under which
about 1,000 staff face pay cuts of Pounds 2,000, on salaries of Pounds
14,000 a year. Next year crews will receive pay rises only if inflation is
above 4 per cent.
BA says its improved compensation package is worth almost Pounds 1,500.
