FT  18 AUG 92 / Parkside mine to close in March
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PARKSIDE, the last coal mine in north-west England, will close in March with
the loss of 720 jobs. The colliery, near Warrington, is the last pit in the
once substantial Lancashire coal field.
Mr Terry Wheatley, group director for British Coal's Midlands and Wales area
which now includes Lancashire, told unions that the colliery, which had been
making substantial losses, had no prospect of survival after March.
