Community, Alice Rawsthorn reports from Paris.
France is committed to maintaining tight control of inflation as the
cornerstone of its economic policy.
July's 0.3 per cent rise compared with an increase of 0.1 per cent in June.
France still has a lower annualised rate of inflation than its main trading
partners, notably Germany with 3.3 per cent, and the US with 3.2 per cent.
