<HEADLINE>
FT  18 AUG 92 / International Company News: Foster's questioned over fall in
share price
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRUCE JACQUES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Australian Stock Exchange yesterday approached directors of Foster's
Brewing Group, the Australian-based international brewer, over the recent
sharp fall in the company's share price.
The shares fell from ADollars 1.82 (USDollars 1.31) on August 10 to a low
point for the year of ADollars 1.65 on August 14, before recovering
yesterday to ADollars 1.70, on speculation centred on Foster's June year
earnings statement, due next month.
Investors have knocked Foster's shares down from a year high of ADollars
2.11, recorded in early June, on fears that the company may announce large
asset write-downs and perhaps be forced to bolster its capital with a share
issue.
The stock exchange asked if Foster's directors believed the company's
earnings would vary by more than 15 per cent over last year and whether it
would record any material abnormal or extraordinary items.
Foster's directors have until midday today - Australian time - to reply.
The share slide also follows Foster's largest shareholder, International
Brewing Holdings, being put into receivership and the apparent lapsing of a
merger proposal from rival beer group, SA Brewing Holdings.
The receivership means a 32 per cent stake parcel in Foster's is for sale,
although the receivers have stated they are prepared to be patient.
</TEXT>
