<HEADLINE>
FT  18 AUG 92 / Letter: Twin tickets
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr SOLOMON MILLER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Jurek Martin ('Fumbling Bush', August 1/2) says US law prohibits a
presidential candidate from choosing a running mate resident in the same
state as himself. This is not so. The 12th Amendment prohibits electors of a
state from voting for a ticket if both candidates are from the electors'
state. But electors from other states could vote. Solomon Miller,
407 Echols Ave,
Huntsville, Alabama, USA.
</TEXT>
